of prank or something?

6
00:00:37,750 --> 00:00:38,541
[TANAKA]
Has to be.

7
00:00:38,625 --> 00:00:39,875
That's the only explanation.

8
00:00:39,958 --> 00:00:41,041
[SOLDIER 21A]
Stay together.

9
00:00:41,125 --> 00:00:42,750
[SOLDIER 21B]
Move, and we shoot.

10
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:43,958
Please, Hayato!

11
00:00:44,041 --> 00:00:45,416
[OURA]
Do something!

12
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,958
[KENTO]
Remain calm.

13
00:00:47,041 --> 00:00:49,625
Do as we tell you,
and no one gets hurt.

14
00:00:49,708 --> 00:00:50,541
[SAKURAKO]
Kento?

15
00:00:50,625 --> 00:00:51,833
[SHOKO]
What the...?

16
00:00:51,916 --> 00:00:54,291
I'm sorry,
but I have my orders.

17
00:00:54,375 --> 00:00:56,416
[IWAGAMI] It is the official
stance of this government

18
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:59,666
that DEAVA represents
a clear and present threat.

19
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:01,083
They are the enemy.

20
00:01:01,166 --> 00:01:04,166
Whereas in Nesta,
Japan has a staunch friend.

21
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,458
DEAVA will be dismantled.

22
00:01:08,541 --> 00:01:11,333
[SUBETE] The Book of Verbalism
exerts irresistible power

23
00:01:11,416 --> 00:01:14,541
over everyone and
everything in its vicinity.

24
00:01:14,625 --> 00:01:17,041
If after uncovering it he'd
gone straight to this country's

25
00:01:17,125 --> 00:01:18,958
heads of state,
my father would have

26
00:01:19,041 --> 00:01:21,250
turned the tide in
his favor from the outset.

27
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:24,833
Alas, he didn't. The fool.

28
00:01:24,916 --> 00:01:26,625
[NESTA]
Come now, Subete.

29
00:01:26,708 --> 00:01:30,166
He refrained
that you might grow.

30
00:01:30,250 --> 00:01:31,583
It's perfect.

31
00:01:31,666 --> 00:01:34,750
The battles,
the agony of defeat...

32
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:36,291
They were necessary.

33
00:01:36,375 --> 00:01:38,625
They are what
brought me to myself!

34
00:01:39,583 --> 00:01:41,458
I will beat Akira.

35
00:01:41,541 --> 00:01:44,875
If his one true desire is
to save the world, well...

36
00:01:44,958 --> 00:01:46,666
I shall be the one to end it.

37
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:48,333
The joy of laughter!

38
00:01:49,625 --> 00:01:52,458
Smiles! Harbingers of happiness.

39
00:01:52,541 --> 00:01:54,625
I crush the very concept!

40
00:01:56,125 --> 00:01:57,916
[SUBETE]
Verbalize and rejoice.

41
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,916
For today I set you free.

42
00:02:00,875 --> 00:02:03,916
An M.J.B.K.
that destroys laughter?

43
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:06,958
Only a first step,
rest assured.

44
00:02:07,041 --> 00:02:09,500
Destroying the very
culture of written language?

45
00:02:09,583 --> 00:02:12,416
That requires Aquarion Logos.

46
00:02:14,208 --> 00:02:15,208
Dear Maia...

47
00:02:15,291 --> 00:02:16,958
Merge with me
and cleanse this world.

48
00:02:17,041 --> 00:02:18,000
[MAIA gasps]

49
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,416
[KENTO] Be smart.
Don't try to resist.

50
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:55,958
