78
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:04,250
[MAIA] Because he's on
the verge of disappearing.

79
00:05:05,416 --> 00:05:07,250
[SUBETE]
Merge with me, Maia.

80
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:08,583
[MAIA]
Never!

81
00:05:08,666 --> 00:05:11,250
I refuse to merge
with someone like you!

82
00:05:11,333 --> 00:05:14,125
And I won't stand by
while Akira vanishes!

83
00:05:19,375 --> 00:05:20,333
[SOLDIER 21C]
What?!

84
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:27,000
[SOLDIER 21A]
Huh?!

85
00:05:27,083 --> 00:05:27,875
[KENTO yells]

86
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:28,708
[SAKURAKO growls]

87
00:05:28,791 --> 00:05:31,000
[SOLDIERS yelling, groaning]

88
00:05:31,625 --> 00:05:33,208
[ALL yelling]

89
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:35,833
Dude, what the hell
just happened up in here?

90
00:05:35,916 --> 00:05:37,250
[SHOKO]
I don't know!

91
00:05:37,333 --> 00:05:39,083
The manager asked me to
launch Vector Two on autopilot,

92
00:05:39,166 --> 00:05:41,083
so I did. That's all, I swear!

93
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:42,958
That was a stupid move!

94
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:46,083
Akira, go!

95
00:05:46,166 --> 00:05:47,708
Right! Yes ma'am!

96
00:05:48,416 --> 00:05:49,375
[HAYATO]
Kaibuki!

97
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:53,041
[SAKURAKO] Vectors and pilots
are bound by Verbalism--

98
00:05:53,125 --> 00:05:54,500
They're drawn to each other.

99
00:05:54,583 --> 00:05:56,583
By sending Vector Two
out on autopilot,

100
00:05:56,666 --> 00:05:58,916
it should seek out Maia for us!

101
00:06:01,958 --> 00:06:03,708
[SUBETE]
What is Vector Two doing here?!

102
00:06:03,791 --> 00:06:05,166
[SUBETE yells]

103
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:07,958
[SUBETE groaning]
Maia, you...

104
00:06:13,416 --> 00:06:14,375
Fire!

105
00:06:17,083 --> 00:06:19,125
[SHOKO squeals]
Get away from me!

106
00:06:19,208 --> 00:06:22,333
You bastard! That's my
woman you're messin' with!

107
00:06:22,416 --> 00:06:23,375
[gunshot]

108
00:06:24,416 --> 00:06:25,375
Crap...

109
00:06:37,041 --> 00:06:38,000
Tsutomu!

110
00:06:39,375 --> 00:06:40,291
[TSUTOMU]
What are you doing?

111
00:06:40,375 --> 00:06:41,416
Get out of his line of fire!

112
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:42,583
[SHOKO]
