253
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:37,958
Maia! Come back!

254
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:41,125
Oh, I see.

255
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:44,416
Genesis Merge!

256
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:47,250
Genesis... Merge.

257
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:48,250
Engrave!

258
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:52,083
Aquarion!

259
00:15:00,791 --> 00:15:03,083
[MAIA]
I'm sorry, Akira.

260
00:15:03,166 --> 00:15:05,041
I know it's wrong, but...

261
00:15:05,125 --> 00:15:07,583
It... It feels...

262
00:15:07,666 --> 00:15:10,041
...so wonderful!

263
00:15:13,833 --> 00:15:15,041
[MAIA, SUBETE]
Ressho!

264
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:23,833
Give me power!

265
00:15:30,416 --> 00:15:32,333
That foolish puppet!

266
00:15:36,041 --> 00:15:38,916
[MAIA gasping]

267
00:15:42,458 --> 00:15:43,250
Maia?

268
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:45,666
[NESTA giggles]
Silly girl.

269
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:47,875
Nesta... No...

270
00:15:49,166 --> 00:15:50,916
She hasn't the
first idea what it costs

271
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,416
to wield my power.

272
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:54,583
Such a desperate move
on her part.

273
00:15:54,666 --> 00:15:56,916
I'm almost moved to pity.

274
00:15:57,000 --> 00:16:00,500
An artificial body like
this could never contain me.

275
00:16:00,583 --> 00:16:03,208
It's far too unstable
to be a proper vessel.

276
00:16:03,291 --> 00:16:05,500
At least, like this.

277
00:16:05,583 --> 00:16:08,541
On the other hand,
raising her power to my level

278
00:16:08,625 --> 00:16:11,791
would make her the perfect
repository for my essence.

279
00:16:11,875 --> 00:16:13,125
Wait! Stop!

280
00:16:13,208 --> 00:16:15,958
What the hell do you think
you're doing to Maia?!

281
00:16:16,041 --> 00:16:18,000
[SUBETE groans]

282
00:16:19,791 --> 00:16:21,791
[SUBETE coughs]

283
00:16:21,875 --> 00:16:23,166
[NESTA]
Oh, dear.

284
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:26,166
Harbor a lingering affection
for the puppet, did we?

285
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:28,916
You ought not push
yourself quite so much.

286
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:32,916
Your friend Akira isn't
the only one short on time.

287
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:35,583
I'm afraid both
of you are doomed.

288
00:16:35,666 --> 00:16:38,333
No! You lie!

289
00:16:38,416 --> 00:16:41,833
Now... Let's get our
little soirée back on track.

290
00:16:44,125 --> 00:16:47,833
Sorry. This party's
about to be over.

291
00:16:47,916 --> 00:16:51,166
Akira! You've got
to destroy this machine!

292
00:16:52,416 --> 00:16:53,666
[MAIA]
Impale Subete.

293
00:16:53,750 --> 00:16:55,000
Don't give a thought to me!

294
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:58,250
I'll die if it lets you
save the world!

295
00:16:58,333 --> 00:17:01,583
It's your only chance! Do it!

296
00:17:03,541 --> 00:17:04,458
Maia...

297
00:17:04,541 --> 00:17:06,458
Are you out of your mind?

298
00:17:06,541 --> 00:17:08,000
You seem worried.

299
00:17:08,083 --> 00:17:11,458
Is it because in a physical body
you can actually be killed?

300
00:17:11,541 --> 00:17:13,833
You whore! This was your plan?

301
00:17:13,916 --> 00:17:16,083
None of us will walk away
from this unscathed,

302
00:17:16,166 --> 00:17:17,791
not even you.

303
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:20,291
You're a puppet! Nothing more!

304
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:23,875
[SAKURAKO]
What?

305
00:17:23,958 --> 00:17:25,875
[SHOKO] The Black Aquarions
are on the move again!

306
00:17:25,958 --> 00:17:29,291
Not good! We can't
get everyone out in time!

307
00:17:29,375 --> 00:17:30,625
[KOKONE]
I'll deal with them!

308
00:17:30,708 --> 00:17:32,625
[SAKURAKO] Kikogami?
What are you thinking?

309
00:17:32,708 --> 00:17:34,625
[KOKONE] I can at least
b-buy us some time.

310
00:17:34,708 --> 00:17:35,833
That's crazy!

311
00:17:35,916 --> 00:17:37,375
You'll be one Vector
against an entire horde!

312
00:17:37,458 --> 00:17:38,791
[MALE STAFF MEMBER 21A]
Another victim here!

313
00:17:38,875 --> 00:17:40,125
[FEMALE STAFF MEMBER 21A]
And a lot more on the way!

314
00:17:40,208 --> 00:17:41,541
[MALE DOCTOR 21A]
Right. Just a moment, please!

315
00:17:41,625 --> 00:17:42,666
[MALE STAFF MEMBER 21B]
Our team's at the ready!

316
00:17:42,750 --> 00:17:45,250
C'mon, guys.
What's with all the noise?

317
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:47,000
[MAIA]
Don't falter, Akira!

318
00:17:47,083 --> 00:17:48,333
We're running out of time.

319
00:17:48,416 --> 00:17:51,083
It's all I can do to keep
her trapped inside me!

320
00:17:51,166 --> 00:17:54,166
Her power's... overwhelming me!

321
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:55,541
Maia, no...

322
00:17:55,625 --> 00:17:59,041
[MAIA] Run us through!
You're the Savior, damn it!

323
00:17:59,125 --> 00:18:00,333
[AKIRA gasps]

324
00:18:00,416 --> 00:18:03,333
If we wait any longer,
more people will die.

325
00:18:05,708 --> 00:18:08,666
[AKIRA] I...
I'll save the entire world!

326
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:10,250
Including you!

327
00:18:19,666 --> 00:18:21,083
That's not possible.

328
00:18:21,166 --> 00:18:23,125
Well I don't believe that!

329
00:18:27,958 --> 00:18:29,333
Please, Akira.

330
00:18:29,416 --> 00:18:31,333
If you end this,
you'll never have to fly

331
00:18:31,416 --> 00:18:34,333
another Vector again, I swear.

332
00:18:34,416 --> 00:18:36,958
You... You won't
have to disappear!

333
00:18:37,041 --> 00:18:39,666
I'm begging you! Please!

334
00:18:44,958 --> 00:18:47,791
[MAIA] If the alternative
is forgetting you,

335
00:18:47,875 --> 00:18:50,750
then I'd honestly
rather be dead.

336
00:18:50,833 --> 00:18:52,333
Do this for me.

337
00:18:53,708 --> 00:18:55,958
[AKIRA]
Don't give in to that bullshit!

338
00:19:03,416 --> 00:19:07,333
[AKIRA growling]

339
00:19:07,416 --> 00:19:08,958
[MAIA]
Damn it, Akira!

340
00:19:09,041 --> 00:19:10,833
[crying]

341
00:19:10,916 --> 00:19:13,125
It's too late to save me,

342
00:19:13,208 --> 00:19:16,083
but you can still
save everyone else!

343
00:19:22,208 --> 00:19:27,166
I can't. I don't have it in me.
I'm not a savior.

344
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:28,458
Akira...

345
00:19:30,541 --> 00:19:31,833
[NESTA]
It's over.

346
00:19:43,791 --> 00:19:45,833
[SHOKO]
No!

347
00:19:48,166 --> 00:19:50,083
It's n-not gonna work.

348
00:19:50,166 --> 00:19:53,083
[TSUTOMU] Now why you gotta
go and make my woman cry?

349
00:19:53,166 --> 00:19:55,541
[KOKONE gasps]
Ts-Tsutomu?

350
00:20:08,375 --> 00:20:11,083
[M.J.B.K. laughing]

351
00:20:11,166 --> 00:20:15,166
[TSUTOMU]
Come on, Hayato. Akira.

352
00:20:15,250 --> 00:20:17,083
Think it's time we merged.

353
00:20:17,166 --> 00:20:18,583
Genesis Merge!

354
00:20:18,666 --> 00:20:22,125
Roar, Aquarion!

355
00:20:35,125 --> 00:20:38,250
[TSUTOMU] Dude. That look
on your face has gotta go.

356
00:20:39,458 --> 00:20:41,166
[TSUTOMU] I mean,
I know there's nothing fun

357
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:43,333
about what's happening
right now, but damn.

358
00:20:43,416 --> 00:20:44,958
[SHOKO]
Tsutomu!

359
00:20:45,041 --> 00:20:46,791
[TSUTOMU]
We have to laugh, man.

360
00:20:46,875 --> 00:20:48,958
Especially in times like this.

361
00:20:49,041 --> 00:20:51,916
That's the
Comedian's Philosophy!

362
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,750
I'm gonna bring 'em back.

363
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:56,041
Every smile in the world.

364
00:20:56,125 --> 00:20:58,375
Tsutomu. Thank you.

365
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:13,000
[M.J.B.K. laughing]

366
00:21:19,541 --> 00:21:21,458
[TSUTOMU, AKIRA, HAYATO]
Amaterasu!

367
00:21:21,541 --> 00:21:25,416
[M.J.B.K. laughing]

368
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:39,208
[MAIA] This light is
so... bright. Beautiful.

369
00:21:39,291 --> 00:21:41,166
It gives me strength.

370
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:55,583
This goes no further.

371
00:21:55,666 --> 00:21:56,708
[NESTA]
Impossible!

372
00:22:04,166 --> 00:22:08,333
[TSUTOMU] I wonder...
Was I able to make Shoko smile?

373
00:22:08,416 --> 00:22:12,041
Seriously.
Girl's got a fantastic one.

374
00:22:12,125 --> 00:22:13,500
I love it.

375
00:22:15,583 --> 00:22:16,708
He did it!

376
00:22:16,791 --> 00:22:19,208
Tsutomu, you beautiful
bastard, you did it!

377
00:22:23,416 --> 00:22:29,541
[KARAN, KOKONE sobbing]

378
00:22:29,625 --> 00:22:32,125
Damn it.

379
00:22:32,208 --> 00:22:33,208
You said...

380
00:22:33,291 --> 00:22:35,208
You were gonna
bring the smiles back.

381
00:22:36,958 --> 00:22:41,000
Where's mine?
Where's my smile?

382
00:22:42,041 --> 00:22:47,541
[SHOKO sobbing]

383
00:24:18,750 --> 00:24:20,958
[KARAN] I just got a gig
for a bonsai-growing show!

384
00:24:21,041 --> 00:24:22,125
[KOKONE]
That's awesome!

385
00:24:22,208 --> 00:24:23,375
[HAYATO]
I may not know how pop idols

386
00:24:23,458 --> 00:24:24,833
normally do it, Karan,
but something tells me

387
00:24:24,916 --> 00:24:26,583
a late-night program
aimed at old people

388
00:24:26,666 --> 00:24:28,541
won't exactly be
your ticket to fame.

389
00:24:28,625 --> 00:24:30,541
[KARAN] I'm trying to reach as
wide an audience as possible,

390
00:24:30,625 --> 00:24:32,250
not just you!

391
00:24:32,333 --> 00:24:33,583
[HAYATO]
Episode 22.

392
00:24:33,666 --> 00:24:35,666
[KOKONE] "Listen! The Voice
Calling Out to You."

393
00:24:35,750 --> 00:24:37,291
I can r-reach out, too!

